As shown in Fig. 5, the limiting current density (Jlim) of the PtNCs and Pt film were 34 and 22 mAcm−2, respectively. It could be observed that the pulse-ECD PtNC CE owned a larger Jlim value of 34 mAcm−2. The PtNC CE displayed an enhanced Jlim, which was in good agreement with the EIS values in terms of Eq. (2) and the lower Rct of the PtNCs. The Jlim also depended on the diffusion coefficient of the I−/I3− redox couples in the DSSCs according to Eq. (3) [16].3D=l2nFCJlim\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
